{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"baking paper","id":"r156334","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-vC7tpRcPsDg\/XZQwxypi-iI\/AAAAAAAAco4\/jTkHGs-druEQW6lHRJ077QbeRgkDbR-AwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_exhhJXqcccSWnXi6.png","title":"Spinach and cheese-filled meatloaf","publishedAt":"2017-05-08T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"content":"20 g extra virgin olive oil, plus extra for greasing"},{"content":"50 g Parmesan cheese, crust removed and cut into pieces (3 cm)"},{"content":"50 g brown onions, cut into halves"},{"content":"1 ½ - 2 garlic cloves, to taste"},{"content":"4 sprigs fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only"},{"content":"40 g breadcrumbs"},{"content":"400 g beef mince"},{"content":"2 eggs"},{"content":"½ tsp freshly ground black pepper"},{"content":"2 tsp salt"},{"content":"50 g Gruyère cheese, cut into slices (2-3 mm)"},{"content":"25 g fresh baby spinach leaves"},{"content":"450 g yellow capsicum, cut into pieces (3-4 cm)"},{"content":"4 - 5 fresh basil, leaves only"},{"content":"400 g chopped tomatoes, canned or fresh cut into pieces (2-3 cm)"},{"content":"200 g water"},{"content":"1 pinch sugar              (optional)"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"35 g","fat":"31 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"18 g","calories":"2128 kJ \/ 508 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Grease Varoma dish and set aside."},{"content":"Place Parmesan cheese, onion, 1 of the garlic cloves and parsley into mixing bowl and chop <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add breadcrumbs, beef mince, eggs, pepper and 1 tsp of the salt and knead <b>1 min\/<b>. Transfer mixture onto a sheet of baking paper (40 cm x 40 cm) and spread out to create a rectangular shape (approx. 25 cm x 20 cm, 1 cm thick). Arrange Gruyère cheese and baby spinach evenly over the meat."},{"content":"Roll up meat with aid of baking paper to create a loaf shape. Remove baking paper and place meatloaf into greased Varoma dish."},{"content":"Place oil, ½-1 garlic cloves, capsicum and basil into mixing bowl and chop <b>4 sec\/speed 5<b>, then sauté <b>3 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add chopped tomatoes, water, remaining 1 tsp salt and sugar (optional), place Varoma into position, secure Varoma lid and cook <b>40 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Set Varoma aside and allow meatloaf to cool for 5 minutes. Meanwhile, <strong>insert measuring cup<\/strong> and blend sauce <b>40 sec\/speed 8<b>. Carefully remove meatloaf from Varoma, cut into slices and serve with sauce."}],"hintsAndTricks":["<i>Now this is not your ordinary meatloaf. Carefully rolled around a Gruyère-spinach filling, gently steamed to preserve a tender and moist interior and served with a fruity tomato and yellow capsicum sauce, it’s excellent both hot and cold. Great for a lunchbox or a picnic, this meatloaf can also be served at an elegant luncheon or a family supper.<\/i>","Gruyère cheese can be replaced with other cheeses (e.g. scamorza, Gouda).<br>- For an easy side dish, in <b>step 6<b> steam up to <b>400 g vegetables<b> (e.g. carrots, potatoes, green beans, courgettes, broccoli), cut in bite-size pieces, in simmering basket. Remove simmering basket when the vegetables are cooked to your liking."],"basicInfo":["medium","25m","1h 15m","4 portions"]}